  "prompt": "What should I wear to prom?",
  "response": "Okay, let's figure out the perfect prom outfit for you!  To give you the best advice, I need a little more information:\n\n**1. What is your personal style?**\n\n*   **Classic & Elegant:** Think timeless silhouettes, luxurious fabrics, and understated glamour.\n*   **Modern & Chic:**  Sleek lines, bold colors, and contemporary details.\n*   **Bohemian & Romantic:** Flowy fabrics, delicate details, and a touch of whimsy.\n*   **Edgy & Bold:**  Unique silhouettes, unexpected textures, and statement accessories.\n*   **Simple & Minimalist:** Clean lines, muted colors, and comfortable fabrics.\n*   **Glamorous & Sparkly:** Sequins, beads, and all-out shine!\n\n**2. What is the prom theme (if any)?**\n\n*   Knowing the theme can help guide your choices (e.g., Hollywood Glamour, Under the Sea, Enchanted Forest, Roaring 20s).\n\n**3. What is your budget?**\n\n*   This will help determine if you're looking to buy new, rent, or shop secondhand.\n\n**4. What makes you feel confident and comfortable?**\n\n*   It's crucial to choose something that makes you feel good about yourself!\n\n**5. What is the dress code of the Prom?**\n*   Is it a black tie affair, or a more casual event?\n\nOnce I have a better understanding of your style, theme, budget, and preferences, I can provide more specific recommendations.\n\n**In the meantime, here are some general ideas and things to consider:**\n\n**Dresses:**\n\n*   **A-Line:** Flattering on most body types. Nips in at the waist and flares out gently.\n*   **Ballgown:** The classic prom dress. Dramatic and formal.\n*   **Mermaid/Trumpet:** Fitted through the bodice and hips, then flares out at the knee.\n*   **Sheath/Column:** Slim and fitted from top to bottom.\n*   **Slip Dress:** Simple, elegant, and can be dressed up or down.\n*   **Two-Piece:** A modern and stylish option.\n*   **Mini/Short Dress:** Can be fun and flirty, but make sure it's appropriate for the venue and your comfort level.\n\n**Suits/Tuxedos (for those who prefer not to wear dresses):**\n\n*   **Classic Black Tuxedo:** A timeless and sophisticated choice.\n*   **Colored Suit:** Navy, burgundy, emerald green, or even a pastel can make a statement.\n*   **Patterned Suit:** Pinstripes, checks, or even floral prints can add personality.\n*   **Velvet Blazer:** Luxurious and eye-catching.\n*   **Consider the fit:** A well-tailored suit is essential.\n\n**Other considerations:**\n\n*   **Color:** Think about colors that complement your skin tone and hair color.\n*   **Fabric:** Consider the weather and the formality of the event. Lighter fabrics like chiffon and lace are good for warmer weather, while heavier fabrics like velvet and satin are better for cooler weather.\n*   **Length:** Choose a length that you feel comfortable and confident in.\n*   **Sleeves:** Sleeveless, short sleeves, long sleeves, or even off-the-shoulder are all options.\n*   **Neckline:** V-neck, scoop neck, halter neck, or strapless are all possibilities.\n*   **Details:** Embellishments like sequins, beads, lace, and embroidery can add visual interest.\n\n**Accessories:**\n\n*   **Shoes:** Comfortable and stylish shoes are a must. Heels, flats, or even dressy sneakers are all options.\n*   **Jewelry:** Choose jewelry that complements your outfit without being overwhelming.\n*   **Clutch/Bag:** A small clutch or bag is perfect for carrying your essentials.\n*   **Hair Accessories:** Headbands, clips, and other hair accessories can add a touch of glamour.\n*   **Corsage/Boutonniere:** Traditional prom accessories.\n\n**Tips for Finding the Perfect Outfit:**\n\n*   **Start planning early:** This gives you plenty of time to shop around and find the perfect outfit.\n*   **Try on different styles:** Even if you think you know what you want, try on a variety of styles to see what looks best on you.\n*   **Don't be afraid to experiment:** Try different colors, fabrics, and silhouettes.\n*   **Get a second opinion:** Bring a friend or family member with you when you shop.\n*   **Make sure it fits properly:** A well-fitting outfit will always look better than one that's too big or too small.\n*   **Consider alterations:** If you find an outfit that you love but it doesn't fit perfectly, consider getting it altered.\n*   **Most importantly, have fun!** Prom is a special occasion, so enjoy the process of finding the perfect outfit.\n\nI'm excited to help you find the perfect prom outfit. Please tell me more about your style, budget, and any other preferences you have. The more information you give me, the better I can assist you!\n",
